Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in South Korea trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:15 a.m. in Seoul.  The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  advanced 22.24, or 1.1 percent, to
2,147.98, rising for a fourth day.  Korea Exchange Bank (004940)  (004940 KS) tumbled 6 percent to 8,960
won, heading for the biggest drop since May 16.  Hana Financial
Group Inc. (086790)  (086790 KS) said it may seek a lower price for its
acquisition of Korea Exchange Bank from Lone Star Funds after
the takeover target decided last week to make a record dividend
payment to the U.S. fund. Hana Financial added 3.4 percent to
38,550 won, poised for the steepest increase since May 20.  Hyundai Motor Co. (005380)  (005380 KS), South Koreaâ€™s largest
automaker, added 1.5 percent to 244,000 won. The company boosted
U.S. sales 16 percent in June to 59,209, while affiliate  Kia
Motors Corp. (000270)  (000270 KS) said its U.S. deliveries jumped 41
percent to 45,044. Kia Motors climbed 2.3 percent to 75,700 won.  To contact the reporter on this story:
